references: We next show algorithms and data structures for the PMDM problem under the assumption that 2ℓsuperscript2ℓ2^{\ell} is reasonably small. Specifically, we consider the word-RAM model with w𝑤w-bit machine words, where w=Ω​(log⁡N+ℓ)𝑤Ω𝑁ℓw\!=\!\Omega(\log\!N+\ell). We measure space in terms of w𝑤w-bit machine words and focus on showing space vs. query-time trade-offs for answering q,z𝑞𝑧q,z PMDM queries over 𝒟𝒟\mathcal{D}. A summary of the complexities of the data structures is shown in Table 1. Specifically, algorithm Small-ℓℓ\ell and data structure Simple are used as building blocks in the more involved data structure Split, shown in the following theorem.

Data structure Simple has lower query time than algorithm Small-ℓℓ\ell. However, its space complexity can be much higher. Data structure Split can be viewed as an intermediate option. For τ𝜏\tau as in Table 1, it has better query time than algorithm Small-ℓℓ\ell for d=ω​(23​ℓ/2)𝑑𝜔superscript23ℓ2d=\omega(2^{3\ell/2}), while keeping moderate space complexity. It always has worse query time than data structure Small, but its space complexity is lower by a factor of 2ℓ/2superscript2ℓ22^{\ell/2}. For example, for d=22​ℓ𝑑superscript22ℓd=2^{2\ell} we get the complexities shown in Table 2.
